  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a5", :ending_coordinate_white => "a6", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 42, :move_number => 3, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "and as in this case the White Pawn is nearer to Queen than any of the Black Pawns, White will  win. Now if it had been Black's move Black could play", :exercise_id => 42, :move_number => 4, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "b7", :ending_coordinate_black => "b6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "c5", :ending_coordinate_white => "b6", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 42, :move_number => 5, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "c7", :ending_coordinate_black => "b6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a5", :ending_coordinate_white => "b6", :explanation => "It would not be advisable to try to obtain a passed Pawn because the White Pawns would be nearer to Queen than the single Black Pawn.", :exercise_id => 42, :move_number => 6, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "a7", :ending_coordinate_black => "b6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a2", :ending_coordinate_white => "a4", :explanation => "The first thing is to find out, by counting, whether the opposing King can be in time to stop the passed Pawn from Queening. When, as in this case, it cannot be done, the point is to count which Pawn comes in first. In this case the time is the same, but the Pawn that reaches the eighth square first and becomes a Queen is in a position to capture the adversary's Queen when he makes one. Thus:", :exercise_id => 43, :move_number => 1, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "h7", :ending_coordinate_black => "h5" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a4", :ending_coordinate_white => "a5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 43, :move_number => 2, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "h5", :ending_coordinate_black => "h4" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "b5", :ending_coordinate_white => "b6", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 43, :move_number => 3, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "a7", :ending_coordinate_black => "b6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a5", :ending_coordinate_white => "a6", :explanation => "Now comes a little calculation. White can capture the Pawn, but if he does so, he will not, when Queening, command the square where Black will also Queen his Pawn. Therefore, instead of taking, he plays:", :exercise_id => 43, :move_number => 4, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "h4", :ending_coordinate_black => "h3" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a6", :ending_coordinate_white => "a7", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 43, :move_number => 5, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "h3", :ending_coordinate_black => "h2" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a7", :ending_coordinate_white => "a8", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 43, :move_number => 6, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "e4", :ending_coordinate_white => "d4", :explanation => "Now Black has the option of either opposing the passage of the White King by playing ♚ - ♛ 3 or, if he prefers, he can pass with his own King by replying ♚ - ♝ 4. Notice that the Kings are directly opposed to each other, and the number of intervening squares between them is odd--one in this case.", :exercise_id => 44, :move_number => 1, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "e1", :ending_coordinate_white => "e2", :explanation => "Now as to the procedure to win such a position. The proper way to begin is to move straight up. Thus:", :exercise_id => 45, :move_number => 1, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "e8", :ending_coordinate_black => "e7" },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "e2", :ending_coordinate_white => "e3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 45, :move_number => 2, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "e7", :ending_coordinate_black => "e6" },
