  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "e4", :ending_coordinate_white => "f4", :explanation => "Now White can exercise the option of either playing ♚ - ♛ 5 and thus passing with his King, or of playing ♚ - ♝ 4 and prevent the Black King from passing, thereby keeping the opposition. Mere counting will show that the former course will only lead to a draw, therefore White takes the latter course and plays:", :exercise_id => 45, :move_number => 4, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "f6", :ending_coordinate_black => "g6" },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "f4", :ending_coordinate_white => "e5", :explanation => "If 4...K - ♚ 3; 5 ♚ - ♞ 5 will win.", :exercise_id => 45, :move_number => 5, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "g6", :ending_coordinate_black => "g7" },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "e1", :ending_coordinate_white => "e2", :explanation => "The process has been comparatively simple in the variation given above, but Black has other lines of  defence more difficult to overcome. Let us begin anew. Now if 2 ♚ - ♛ 3, ♚ - ♛ 2, or if 2 ♚ - ♚ 3, ♚ - ♚ 2, and Black obtains the opposition in both cases. (When the Kings are directly in front of one another, and the number of intervening squares between the Kings is odd, the player who has moved last has the opposition.)", :exercise_id => 46, :move_number => 1, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "e8", :ending_coordinate_black => "d8" },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "e2", :ending_coordinate_white => "f3", :explanation => "Now in order to win, the White King must advance. There is only one other square where he can go, ♝ 3, and that is the right place. Therefore it is seen that in such cases when the opponent makes a so-called waiting move, you must advance, leaving a rank or file free between the Kings. Therefore we have--", :exercise_id => 46, :move_number => 2, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "d8", :ending_coordinate_black => "e7" },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "f3", :ending_coordinate_white => "e8", :explanation => "Now, it would be bad to advance, because then Black, by bringing up his King in front of your King, would obtain the opposition. It is White's turn to play a similar move to Black's first move, viz.:", :exercise_id => 46, :move_number => 3, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "g2", :ending_coordinate_white => "h1", :explanation => "White is a Pawn behind and apparently lost, yet he can manage to draw as follows:", :exercise_id => 47, :move_number => 1, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "The position of the Pawns does not permit White to draw by means of the actual or close opposition, hence he takes the distant opposition: in effect if 1 ♚ - ♝ 1 (actual or close opposition), ♚ - ♛ 7; 2 ♚ - ♝ 2, ♚ - ♛ 6 and White cannot continue to keep the lateral opposition essential to his safety, because of his own Pawn at ♝ 3. On the other hand, after the text move, if", :exercise_id => 47, :move_number => 2, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:21", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "d1", :ending_coordinate_black => "d2" },
