  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "b2", :ending_coordinate_white => "b4", :explanation => "Now suppose that in the position in the preceding diagram it were Black's move, and he played ♜ - ♚ ♝ 1. White would then simply defend his ♚ ♝ ♟ by some move like ♛ - ♚ ♝ 3, threatening ♜ x ♛ ♝ ♟, and then he would bring his King up to ♞ 3, and when the time came, break through, as in the previous case. White might even be able to obtain the following position:", :exercise_id => 89, :move_number => 11, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
