  { :piece_white => "♜", :starting_coordinate_white => "a1", :ending_coordinate_white => "c1", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 14, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "White is perfectly developed, and now threatens to win a Pawn as follows: ♞ x ♞, ♞ x ♞; ♟ - ♚ 4, followed by ♜ x ♟.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 15, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "c7", :ending_coordinate_black => "c6" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "c3", :ending_coordinate_white => "e4", :explanation => "The fact that Black is practically forced to make this move in order to avoid the loss of a Pawn is sufficient reason in itself to condemn the whole system of development on Black's part. In effect, he plays ♝ - ♛ 2 and now he has to shut off the action of his  own Bishop, which thereby becomes little more than a Pawn for a while. In fact, it is hard to see how this Bishop will ever be able to attack anything. Besides, it can be easily seen that White will soon post his two Knights at ♚ 5 and ♛ ♝ 5 respectively, and that Black will not be able to dislodge them without seriously weakening his game, if he can do it at all. From all these reasons it can be gathered that it would probably have been better for Black to play ♞ x ♞ and thus get rid of one of the two White Knights before assuming such a defensive position. In such cases, the less the number of pieces on the board, the better chances there are to escape.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 16, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "f7", :ending_coordinate_black => "f5" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "e4", :ending_coordinate_white => "c5", :explanation => "This practically amounts to committing suicide, since it creates a hole at ♚ 5 for White's Knight, from where it will be practically impossible to dislodge him. If Black intended to make such a move he should have done it before, when at least there would have been an object in preventing the White Knight from reaching ♝ 5.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 17, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♝", :starting_coordinate_black => "d7", :ending_coordinate_black => "e8" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "f3", :ending_coordinate_white => "e5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 18, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "The position of White's Knights, especially the one at ♚ 5, might be said to be ideal, and a single glance shows how they dominate the position. The question henceforth will be how is White going to derive the full benefit from such an advantageous situation, This we shall soon see.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 19, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "a8", :ending_coordinate_black => "b8" },
  { :piece_white => "♜", :starting_coordinate_white => "f1", :ending_coordinate_white => "e1", :explanation => "There is no object in this move, unless it is to be followed by ♞ - ♛ 2. As that is not the case, he might have gone with the Rook to ♝ 1, as he does later.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 20, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "f8", :ending_coordinate_black => "f6" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "d1", :ending_coordinate_white => "f3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 21, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "f6", :ending_coordinate_black => "h6" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "f3", :ending_coordinate_white => "g3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 22, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "b8", :ending_coordinate_black => "c8" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "f2", :ending_coordinate_white => "f3", :explanation => "White threatened to win the exchange by playing either ♞ - ♝ 7 or ♞ - ♞ 4.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 23, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "c8", :ending_coordinate_black => "c7" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a2", :ending_coordinate_white => "a3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 24, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "g8", :ending_coordinate_black => "h8" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "h2", :ending_coordinate_white => "h3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 25, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "♟erhaps all these precautions are unnecessary, but White feels that he has more than enough time to prepare his attack, and wants to be secure in every way before he begins.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 26, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "g7", :ending_coordinate_black => "g5" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "e3", :ending_coordinate_white => "e4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 27, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "f5", :ending_coordinate_black => "f4" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "g3", :ending_coordinate_white => "f2", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 28, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "d5", :ending_coordinate_black => "e3" },
  { :piece_white => "♜", :starting_coordinate_white => "e1", :ending_coordinate_white => "e3", :explanation => "He had better have played ♞ - ♝ 3; and tried later on to get rid of White's Knights by means of ♞ - ♛ 2.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 29, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "with this sacrifice of the Rook for a Knight and Pawn White obtains an overwhelming position.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 30, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "f4", :ending_coordinate_black => "e3" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "f2", :ending_coordinate_white => "e3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 31, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "b6", :ending_coordinate_black => "c8" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "e5", :ending_coordinate_white => "g4", :explanation => "♞ - ♛ 2 was better in order to get rid of one of the two White Knights. There were, however, any number of good replies to it, among them the following: ♞ (♝ 5) x ♞, ♝ x ♞; ♛ x ♟, ♛ x ♛; ♞ - ♝ 7 ch, ♚ - ♞ 2; ♞ x ♛, and with two Pawns for the exchange, and the position so much in his favour, White should have no trouble in winning.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 32, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "h6", :ending_coordinate_black => "g6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "e4", :ending_coordinate_white => "e5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 33, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "g6", :ending_coordinate_black => "g7" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "d3", :ending_coordinate_white => "c4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 34, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♝", :starting_coordinate_black => "e8", :ending_coordinate_black => "f7" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "g4", :ending_coordinate_white => "f6", :explanation => "All these moves are practically forced, and as it is easily seen they tie up Black's position more and more. White's manoeuvres from move 24 onwards are highly instructive.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 35, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "c8", :ending_coordinate_black => "b6" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "c5", :ending_coordinate_white => "e4", :explanation => "This wandering Knight has done nothing throughout the game.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 36, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "h7", :ending_coordinate_black => "h6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "h3", :ending_coordinate_white => "h4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 37, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "b6", :ending_coordinate_black => "d5" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "e3", :ending_coordinate_white => "d2", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 38, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "g7", :ending_coordinate_black => "g6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "h4", :ending_coordinate_white => "g5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 39, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♛", :starting_coordinate_black => "e7", :ending_coordinate_black => "f8" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "f3", :ending_coordinate_white => "f4", :explanation => "If ♟ x ♟; ♚ - ♝ 2, and Black would be helpless.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 40, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "d5", :ending_coordinate_black => "e7" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "g2", :ending_coordinate_white => "g4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 41, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "h6", :ending_coordinate_black => "g5" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "f4", :ending_coordinate_white => "g5", :explanation => "There is nothing to be done. If ♝ - ♞ 1; ♛ - ♜ 2 ch, ♚ - ♞ 2; ♝ x ♟.", :exercise_id => 90, :move_number => 42, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "d2", :ending_coordinate_white => "d4", :explanation => "White: F. J. Marshall. Black: J. ♜. Capablanca.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 1, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "d7", :ending_coordinate_black => "d5" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "c2", :ending_coordinate_white => "c4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 2, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "e7", :ending_coordinate_black => "e6" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "b1", :ending_coordinate_white => "c3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 3, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "g8", :ending_coordinate_black => "f6" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "c1", :ending_coordinate_white => "g5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 4, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♝", :starting_coordinate_black => "f8", :ending_coordinate_black => "e7" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "e2", :ending_coordinate_white => "e3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 5, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "f6", :ending_coordinate_black => "e4" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "g5", :ending_coordinate_white => "e7", :explanation => "I had played this defence twice before in the match with good results, and although I lost this game I still played it until the very last game, when I changed my tactics. The reason was my total lack of knowledge of the different variations in this opening, coupled with the fact that I knew that Dr. E. Lasker had been successful with it against Marshall himself in 1907. I thought that since Dr. Lasker had played it so often, it should be good. The object is to exchange a couple of pieces and at the same time to bring about a position full of possibilities and with promising chances of success once the end-game stage is reached. On general principles it should be wrong, because the  same Knight is moved three times in the opening, although it involves the exchange of two pieces. In reality the difficulty in this variation, as well as in nearly all the variations of the Queen's gambit, lies in the slow development of Black's Queen Bishop. However, whether this variation can or cannot be safely played is a question still to be decided, and it is outside the scope of this book. I may add that at present my preference is for a different system of development, but it is not unlikely that I should some time come back to this variation.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 6, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♛", :starting_coordinate_black => "d8", :ending_coordinate_black => "e7" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "f1", :ending_coordinate_white => "d3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 7, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "♟ x ♟ is preferable for reasons that we shall soon see.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 8, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "e4", :ending_coordinate_black => "c3" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "b2", :ending_coordinate_white => "c3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 9, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "b8", :ending_coordinate_black => "d7" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "g1", :ending_coordinate_white => "f3", :explanation => "Now ♟ x ♟ would be a better way to develop the game. The idea is that after 8...♟ x ♟; 9 ♝ x ♝ ♟, ♟ - ♛ ♞ 3, followed by ♝ - ♞ 2, would give Black's Bishop a powerful range. For this variation see the eleventh game of the match.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 10, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "e8", :ending_coordinate_black => "g8" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "c4", :ending_coordinate_white => "d5", :explanation => "No longer would 9...♟ x ♟; 10 ♝ x ♟, ♟ - ♛ ♞ 3 be good, because 11 ♝ - ♞ 5 would prevent ♝ - ♞ 2 on account of ♞ - ♚ 5.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 11, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "e6", :ending_coordinate_black => "d5" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "d1", :ending_coordinate_white => "b3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 12, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "d7", :ending_coordinate_black => "f6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a2", :ending_coordinate_white => "a4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 13, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "c7", :ending_coordinate_black => "c5" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "b3", :ending_coordinate_white => "a3", :explanation => "♟layed with the intention of obtaining the majority of Pawns on the Queen's side. Yet it is doubtful whether this move is good, since it leaves Black's Queen's-side Pawns disrupted in a way. The safer course would have been to play ♟ - ♝ 3.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 14, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "b5", :ending_coordinate_black => "b6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a4", :ending_coordinate_white => "a5", :explanation => "This exposes Black to further attack by ♟ - ♜ 5 without any compensation for it. If I had to play this position nowadays I would simply play 13...R - ♚ 1. Then after 14 ♛ x ♟, ♛ x ♛ would follow, and I believe that Black would regain the Pawn. If, instead, White played 14 ♟ x ♟ then ♝ - ♞ 5 would give Black an excellent game.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 15, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♝", :starting_coordinate_black => "c8", :ending_coordinate_black => "b7" },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "d1", :ending_coordinate_white => "g1", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 16, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♛", :starting_coordinate_black => "e7", :ending_coordinate_black => "c7" },
  { :piece_white => "♜", :starting_coordinate_white => "f1", :ending_coordinate_white => "b1", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 17, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "f6", :ending_coordinate_black => "d7" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "d3", :ending_coordinate_white => "f5", :explanation => "Black's position was bad and perhaps lost in any case, but the text move makes matters worse. As a matter of fact I never saw White's reply ♝ - ♝ 5. It never even passed through my mind that this was threatened. Black's best move would have been 16...K ♜ - ♞ 1. If that loses, then any other move would lose as well.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 18, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "f8", :ending_coordinate_black => "c8" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "f5", :ending_coordinate_white => "d7", :explanation => "From bad to worse. ♞ - ♝ 3 offered the only hope.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 19, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:22", :piece_black => "♛", :starting_coordinate_black => "e7", :ending_coordinate_black => "d7" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "a5", :ending_coordinate_white => "a6", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 20, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♝", :starting_coordinate_black => "b7", :ending_coordinate_black => "c6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "d4", :ending_coordinate_white => "c5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 21, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "d6", :ending_coordinate_black => "c5" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "a3", :ending_coordinate_white => "c5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 22, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "a8", :ending_coordinate_black => "b8" },
  { :piece_white => "♜", :starting_coordinate_white => "b1", :ending_coordinate_white => "b8", :explanation => "The game was lost. One move was as good as another.", :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 23, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "c8", :ending_coordinate_black => "b8" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "f3", :ending_coordinate_white => "e5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 24, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♛", :starting_coordinate_black => "d7", :ending_coordinate_black => "f5" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "f3", :ending_coordinate_white => "f4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 91, :move_number => 25, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "b8", :ending_coordinate_black => "b6" },
