  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "d2", :ending_coordinate_white => "d3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 6, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "e4", :ending_coordinate_black => "f6" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "c1", :ending_coordinate_white => "g5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 7, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "♟layed by Morphy, and a very fine move. The point is that should Black exchange Queens he will be a move behind in development and consequently will get a cramped game if White plays accurately.", :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 8, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♝", :starting_coordinate_black => "c8", :ending_coordinate_black => "e6" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "b1", :ending_coordinate_white => "c3", :explanation => "Marshall thought at the time that this was the best move and consequently played it in preference to ♛ x ♛ ch.", :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 9, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "h7", :ending_coordinate_black => "h6" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "g5", :ending_coordinate_white => "f6", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 10, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♛", :starting_coordinate_black => "e7", :ending_coordinate_black => "f6" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "d3", :ending_coordinate_white => "d4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 11, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♝", :starting_coordinate_black => "f8", :ending_coordinate_black => "e7" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "e2", :ending_coordinate_white => "b5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 12, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♞", :starting_coordinate_black => "b7", :ending_coordinate_black => "d7" },
  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "f1", :ending_coordinate_white => "d3", :explanation => "It is now time to examine the result of the opening. On White's side we find the minor pieces well posted and the Queen out in a somewhat odd place, it is true, but safe from attack and actually attacking a Pawn.  White is also ready to Castle. White's position is evidently free from danger and his pieces can easily manoeuvre.", :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 13, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "On Black's side the first thing we notice is that he has retained both his Bishops, unquestionably an advantage; but on the other hand we find his pieces bunched together too much, and the Queen in danger of being attacked without having any good square to go to. The Bishop at ♚ 2 has no freedom and it blocks the Queen, which, in its turn, blocks the Bishop. Besides, Black cannot Castle on the King's side because ♛ x ♟, ♜ - ♞ 1; ♛ - ♚ 4 threatening mate, wins a Pawn. Nor can he Castle on the Queen's side because ♛ - ♜ 5 would put Black's game in imminent danger, since he cannot play ♟ - ♜ 3 because of ♝ x ♟; nor can he play ♚ - ♞ 1 because of ♞ - ♞ 5. Consequently we must conclude that the opening is all in White's favour.", :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 14, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "g2", :ending_coordinate_black => "g5" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "h2", :ending_coordinate_white => "h3", :explanation => "To make room for his Queen, threatening also ♟ - ♞ 5.", :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 15, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "e8", :ending_coordinate_black => "g8" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "b5", :ending_coordinate_white => "b7", :explanation => "giving up a Pawn in an attempt to free his game and take the initiative. It was difficult for him to find a move, as White threatened ♞ - ♚ 4, and should Black go with the Queen to ♞ 2, then ♟ - ♛ 5, ♝ - ♝ 4; ♞ x ♟ ch, followed by ♝ x ♝.", :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 16, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♜", :starting_coordinate_black => "a8", :ending_coordinate_black => "b8" },
  { :piece_white => "♛", :starting_coordinate_white => "b7", :ending_coordinate_white => "e4", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 17, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♛", :starting_coordinate_black => "f6", :ending_coordinate_black => "g7" },
  { :piece_white => "♟", :starting_coordinate_white => "b2", :ending_coordinate_white => "b3", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 18, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "c7", :ending_coordinate_black => "c5" },
  { :piece_white => "♚", :starting_coordinate_white => "d1", :ending_coordinate_white => "g1", :explanation => "In order to break up White's centre and bring his Knight to ♝ 4 and thus lay the foundation for a violent attack against White's King. The plan, however, fails, as it always must in such cases, because Black's development is backward, and consequently his pieces are not properly placed.", :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 19, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "c5", :ending_coordinate_black => "d4" },
  { :piece_white => "♞", :starting_coordinate_white => "c3", :ending_coordinate_white => "d5", :explanation => nil, :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 20, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 21:14:07", :piece_black => "...", :starting_coordinate_black => nil, :ending_coordinate_black => nil },
  { :piece_white => "...", :starting_coordinate_white => nil, :ending_coordinate_white => nil, :explanation => "A simple move, which destroys Black's plan utterly. Black will now have no concerted action of his pieces, and, as his Pawns are all weak, he will sooner or later lose them.", :exercise_id => 92, :move_number => 21, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♝", :starting_coordinate_black => "e7", :ending_coordinate_black => "d8" },
