  { :piece_white => "♜", :starting_coordinate_white => "f5", :ending_coordinate_white => "f7", :explanation => "A bad move, which gives away any legitimate chance Black had to draw. It loses a very important move. In fact, as the course of the game will show, it loses several moves. The proper way was to play ♚ - ♛ 3. If then ♜ - ♛ ♞ 5, ♜ x ♜; ♝ x ♜, ♞ - ♛ 5; followed by ♟ - ♛ ♞ 4; and White would have an exceedingly difficult game to draw on account of the dominating position of the Knight at  ♛ 5 in conjunction with the extra Pawn on the Queen's side and the awkward position of White's King. (See how this is so.)", :exercise_id => 97, :move_number => 34, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:23", :piece_black => "♚", :starting_coordinate_black => "d7", :ending_coordinate_black => "d6" },
