  { :piece_white => "♝", :starting_coordinate_white => "h6", :ending_coordinate_white => "g7", :explanation => "Most players will be wondering, as the spectators did, why I did not resign. The reason is that while I knew the game to be lost, I was hoping for the following variation, which Chajes came very near playing: 51 ♛ x ♟ ch, ♚ - ♜ 2; 52 ♛ - ♜ 5, ♜ x ♟; 53 ♝ - ♞ 5 ch, ♚ - ♞ 2; 54 ♝ x ♜ ch, ♚ x ♝; and while White has a won game it is by no means easy. If the reader does not believe it, let him take the White pieces against a master and see what happens. My opponent, who decided to take no chances, played 51 ♝ - ♞ 7, and finally won as shown below.", :exercise_id => 101, :move_number => 57, :computer => nil, :created_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:24", :updated_at => "2013-07-17 20:41:24", :piece_black => "♟", :starting_coordinate_black => "g4", :ending_coordinate_black => "g3" },
